	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001174_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="8" unit="chars"/><placeName>50 Albemarle <choice><abbr>St</abbr><expan>Street</expan></choice></placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="8" unit="chars"/><date when="1858-01-11">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Jany</abbr><expan>January</expan></choice> 1858</date> </p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Sir </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="7" unit="chars"/>I found that 
<lb/>I could not manage 
<lb/>so as to write a 
<lb/>letter to the <bibl>Statesman</bibl> 
<lb/>though your <bibl>letter</bibl> 
<lb/>has been lying 
<lb/>constantly before 
<lb/>me since the <date when="1857-12-25">25<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="la"><choice><abbr>Ult.</abbr><expan>Ultimo</expan></choice></foreign></date> I quite agree 
<lb/>in all you advance 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001174_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>but my time is 
<lb/>so fully occupied 
<lb/>in preparation that 
<lb/>I can not sit down 
<lb/>to any thing except 
<lb/>those connected 
<lb/>with my own 
<lb/>expedition. I 
<lb/>heartily wish you 
<lb/>success in your 
<lb/>noble undertaking 
<lb/>and am glad to see 
<lb/>your advertisements 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001174_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/>increasing in number
<lb/>All blessings on you 
<lb/>and yours from </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/>Yours ever </p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>T. Ballantyne Esq</persName></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001174_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
